      },
      "date": "2020-02-12 17:30:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1\n\nWow, that's a whole lot of failin' goin' on. \n\nIt makes me wonder if we can't isolate this to a specific patch that started the problems, since I thought we had PPC sanity almost passing at one point?  I've isolated the PFL failures to the xattr swabbing patch that was fixing other PPC problems, but I can't imagine that it could have passed testing and then landed and caused so many problems.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "598a7a889f89c3a1a89cdfef5182230f4179d2fb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-02-12 17:58:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\nSee my comments in LU-13232.  I suspect there is a much less drastic solution to these failures. That would ensure more of the tests keep running on PPC, and are less likely to introduce additional regressions due to so many tests being skipped.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
